&s;hepherde&s;s.</P>
<P>Ferdinand was, or pretended to be, the la&s;t
per&s;on in the family, who under&s;tood the &s;itua|tion
of her thoughts; when he perceived her
pa&s;&s;ion, he entered into deliberation with him|&s;elf,
