effectually e&s;pou&s;e his cau&s;e, and employ her
good offices with her mi&s;tre&s;s, in his behalf:
be&s;ides, he was induced by another motive,
which though &s;econdary, did not fail in this ca&s;e
to have an effect upon his determination. He
