in point of warmth and particular com|placency
to the love-&s;ick maid.</P>
<P>He fir&s;t of all, thanked her in the mo&s;t grate|ful
terms, for the concern &s;he had manife&s;ted at
his di&s;temper, and the kind &s;ervices he had re|ceived
