much intendered to hold out again&s;t all the forms
<PB N="39" REF="48">
of a&s;&s;ault, far from yielding at di&s;cretion, &s;he
&s;tood upon honourable terms, with great ob&s;ti|nacy
of punctilio, and while &s;he owned he was
