<P>Such a ba&s;e declaration our hero would not have
ventured to make, had he not implicitly believed
the dam&s;el was as great a latitudinarian as him|&s;elf
in point of morals and principle; and been
well a&s;&s;ured that though he &s;hould be mi&s;taken
