of Hungary, eccle&s;ia&s;tics are more &s;cru|pulous
in the exerci&s;e of their function, and the
objection was, or &s;uppo&s;ed to be altogether in|&s;urmountable;
&s;o that they were fain to have
recour&s;e to an expedient, with which, after &s;ome
he&s;itation, our &s;he-adventurer was &s;atisfied. They
